1
00:00:29,129 --> 00:00:32,644
- You've done this before. Obviously.
- No.

2
00:00:32,849 --> 00:00:34,965
Oh, God. Obviously.

3
00:00:35,729 --> 00:00:38,448
- I have to go back to work.
- No.

4
00:00:38,729 --> 00:00:41,766
- You don't have to go to work.
- Yes, I do.

5
00:00:41,969 --> 00:00:43,925
- It's time.
- No, no.

6
00:00:44,129 --> 00:00:46,518
Wait a minute. Just...

7
00:00:46,729 --> 00:00:48,799
Just give me 10 minutes more.

8
00:00:49,009 --> 00:00:51,364
Fifteen, 20 minutes more?
Come on.

9
00:00:51,609 --> 00:00:54,760
- I want to show you something.
- What?

10
00:00:54,969 --> 00:00:56,960
What's this?
How does this work?

11
00:00:57,169 --> 00:00:59,319
Am I supposed to twist it
or something?

12
00:00:59,569 --> 00:01:00,843
Was that you?

13
00:01:01,049 --> 00:01:03,244
We're experiencing turbulence.

14
00:01:03,449 --> 00:01:05,644
Please fasten your seat belts.

15
00:01:06,169 --> 00:01:08,125
Can you get me a cup of coffee?

16
00:01:08,329 --> 00:01:10,843
- No problem.
- Prepare for landing.

17
00:01:11,129 --> 00:01:14,439
I have to get to work.
We'll land in 30 minutes.

18
00:01:20,049 --> 00:01:22,563
I'm a frequent flyer,
I got a bonus.

19
00:01:23,409 --> 00:01:24,478
Good morning.

20
00:01:24,689 --> 00:01:28,807
We are approaching Chicago's
O'Hare International Airport.

21
00:01:29,009 --> 00:01:34,037
Please extinguish all cigarettes.
Return seats to the upright position.

22
00:01:39,569 --> 00:01:41,878
The local time is 8:10 am.

23
00:01:42,089 --> 00:01:45,764
On behalf of our crew, thank you
for flying Trans Allied...

24
00:01:45,969 --> 00:01:49,325
...the official airline
of the Indiana Pacers.

25
00:03:44,009 --> 00:03:47,365
- Sign for no lights at Wrigley Field.
- I've signed.

26
00:03:47,569 --> 00:03:49,560
No lights at Wrigley Field.

27
00:03:49,809 --> 00:03:52,448
From Davenport?
One of the quad cities?

28
00:03:52,689 --> 00:03:55,567
Twice as good as the Twin Cities.
Good luck.

29
00:03:55,769 --> 00:03:57,919
Matty and Matty,
maintenance men.

30
00:03:58,129 --> 00:04:01,644
What are the odds of that?
Two Mattys in one building.

31
00:04:01,849 --> 00:04:03,999
Polly, still pushing grapes.

32
00:04:04,209 --> 00:04:06,723
Is she filling out an application?

33
00:04:06,929 --> 00:04:10,205
Don't! It's hell through these doors!

34
00:04:10,409 --> 00:04:14,197
Hi, Kathy. Tell that lady
the truth about advertising.

35
00:04:14,409 --> 00:04:15,888
BG and L hell!

36
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:19,047
Here's the guys
who are working very hard.

37
00:04:20,129 --> 00:04:22,927
Right inside.
It's all I can spare today.

38
00:04:23,129 --> 00:04:24,687
- Thanks, dude.
- Mr. Basner.

39
00:04:24,889 --> 00:04:28,325
Two examples for labor laws.
Check out the talent.

40
00:04:28,529 --> 00:04:30,645
I'm back! Remember me?

41
00:04:31,089 --> 00:04:33,444
They're in there.
Thanks, Donovan.

42
00:04:33,649 --> 00:04:36,368
Here's a gift from the Bahamas.
Why?

43
00:04:36,569 --> 00:04:40,084
Because you crack me up.
You make me laugh.

44
00:04:40,289 --> 00:04:42,883
Is this red tie day?
Nobody told me.

45
00:04:43,089 --> 00:04:46,365
- Bloody Friday.
- Hear what happened to Clemens?

46
00:04:46,609 --> 00:04:49,521
- He got terminated.
- We fired Clemens?

47
00:04:49,729 --> 00:04:51,367
I'm sorry to hear that.

48
00:04:51,889 --> 00:04:54,244
He was an asshole. Come on.

49
00:04:54,449 --> 00:04:56,883
- Dave? How are you?
- All right.

50
00:04:57,089 --> 00:04:59,523
Congratulations on the promotion.

51
00:04:59,729 --> 00:05:03,358
That's big of you.
Is today your birthday?

52
00:05:04,089 --> 00:05:07,638
- Welcome back, Basner.
- You want to see my tan line?

53
00:05:07,929 --> 00:05:12,081
Clemens is gone. Rumor has it
he stored drugs in his cubicle.

54
00:05:12,289 --> 00:05:14,564
- Slice his chair.
- Get airport dogs.

55
00:05:14,729 --> 00:05:17,243
Doris, did you miss me? Of course.

56
00:05:19,009 --> 00:05:21,603
Thanks for the quickie.
You wear me out.

57
00:05:21,809 --> 00:05:23,686
Put it out. I see the smoke.

58
00:05:23,889 --> 00:05:27,404
Where are our best and brightest?
Our creative aspect.

59
00:05:27,649 --> 00:05:30,641
- The boss is back.
- You don't check anything.

60
00:05:30,849 --> 00:05:32,726
Welcome back, Mr. Basner.

61
00:05:32,929 --> 00:05:37,241
You have 10 urgent messages,
but you're due in the conference room.

62
00:05:37,449 --> 00:05:39,804
Get this fixed. It almost killed me.

63
00:05:40,009 --> 00:05:43,240
- Who's got a team?
- We got a team!

64
00:05:43,449 --> 00:05:45,724
Dale, Rick, Brian, Cameron, Mishi...

65
00:05:45,929 --> 00:05:49,717
- Who knows where your lips have been.
- How's the Bahamas?

66
00:05:49,929 --> 00:05:52,887
You wouldn't like diving.
You can't smoke.

67
00:05:53,089 --> 00:05:56,047
This is adorable.
Brian, that was great.

68
00:05:56,249 --> 00:05:58,240
- Who locked it?
- It's a joke.

69
00:05:58,529 --> 00:06:01,089
It's an office.
Let's lose the plant.

70
00:06:01,289 --> 00:06:04,679
- Look at this. It's a man's desk!
- Bring any presents?

71
00:06:04,889 --> 00:06:06,766
I have gifts for all...

72
00:06:06,969 --> 00:06:11,360
...including a figurehead
from a ship 300 feet below the sea.

73
00:06:11,609 --> 00:06:13,088
That's for me. What?

74
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:16,281
An office with a window.

75
00:06:37,929 --> 00:06:42,047
Oh, for me? This is lovely!
We don't handle these people.

76
00:06:42,249 --> 00:06:44,763
I can see traffic accidents.

77
00:06:44,969 --> 00:06:46,880
- Okay, staff!
- Listen up.

78
00:06:47,089 --> 00:06:50,525
Guys and gals,
the first order of business is: Out.

79
00:06:50,849 --> 00:06:52,077
No work right now.

80
00:06:52,289 --> 00:06:54,359
I love short meetings.

81
00:06:54,609 --> 00:06:57,760
I went shopping.
New office, clothes, new image.

82
00:06:57,969 --> 00:07:00,608
- We have a meeting.
- I won't forget.

83
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:38,048
Talk to me about it.
Somebody, anybody.

84
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:40,001
The account loves it.

85
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:43,997
Tests show it does big.
Especially in our target, Europe.

86
00:07:44,209 --> 00:07:47,645
- You do nice work.
- He should, with that raise.

87
00:07:47,889 --> 00:07:50,608
That's it. Thank you very much.
Let's go.

88
00:07:50,809 --> 00:07:52,367
Now, about that lunch...

89
00:07:52,689 --> 00:07:56,762
No, do that, and put the memo
on my desk in my new office.

90
00:07:57,009 --> 00:07:58,727
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

91
00:07:58,929 --> 00:08:01,841
Donovan, play that back for me, okay?

92
00:08:05,249 --> 00:08:07,604
No, don't, Donovan.
David...

93
00:08:07,809 --> 00:08:11,119
...I know you've received
two offers from agencies.

94
00:08:11,329 --> 00:08:14,321
Decline, or I'll
throw you out your window.

95
00:08:14,569 --> 00:08:16,878
Why? They won't make me a partner.

96
00:08:17,129 --> 00:08:18,608
Partner?

97
00:08:19,049 --> 00:08:21,802
Boile, Gargas, Lionel and Basner?

98
00:08:22,009 --> 00:08:24,364
Like John, Paul, George and Ringo.

99
00:08:24,609 --> 00:08:27,885
- You're pretty cocky.
- No, just pretty capable.

100
00:08:28,369 --> 00:08:31,202
In creating cute
and flashy commercials.

101
00:08:32,009 --> 00:08:36,321
- You have to bring in new accounts.
- Just watch me.

102
00:08:37,129 --> 00:08:39,563
Here's one. Make it up right there.

103
00:08:43,329 --> 00:08:44,808
You pay him!

104
00:08:45,009 --> 00:08:48,922
- I'm dancing, I'm not embarrassed.
- You're drunk.

105
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:50,767
I'm having a drink.

106
00:08:52,009 --> 00:08:52,964
Run it by.

107
00:08:53,609 --> 00:08:55,759
Yo, Davey!

108
00:08:55,969 --> 00:08:57,800
Meet Sheila and Louise.

109
00:08:58,009 --> 00:08:59,442
- Louise.
- Great.

110
00:08:59,649 --> 00:09:02,038
Did you lose the wedding ring?

111
00:09:02,249 --> 00:09:05,127
- This is Sam.
- Nice to meet you.

112
00:09:05,609 --> 00:09:09,079
I'm glad you got the job. I mean it.

113
00:09:09,289 --> 00:09:12,361
- Will you drive him?
- What will I tell my folks?

114
00:09:13,369 --> 00:09:16,042
- Jo-Jo, give me a stout.
- Beer's on us.

115
00:09:16,649 --> 00:09:19,004
Thank you. Hey, nice... What?

116
00:09:19,209 --> 00:09:22,167
- Burnett Agency hot shots.
- Jo-Jo's on it.

117
00:09:22,369 --> 00:09:24,519
That's why you're the boss.

118
00:09:25,889 --> 00:09:29,438
Some big outfit
wants to switch ad agencies.

119
00:09:29,649 --> 00:09:32,322
What big outfit?
Their computer line? Cosmetics?

120
00:09:32,569 --> 00:09:35,037
- It's an airline.
- Well, which one?

121
00:09:35,249 --> 00:09:38,844
- I'll drop a microphone in the drinks.
- Just find out.

122
00:09:39,049 --> 00:09:43,008
- I'll fix you up with Cameron, okay?
- Yeah.

123
00:09:43,209 --> 00:09:45,359
Just don't be too obvious.

124
00:09:45,649 --> 00:09:48,641
Go easy on him.
I need him at the office.

125
00:09:48,849 --> 00:09:49,918
Another round?

126
00:09:51,689 --> 00:09:53,680
I gotta run. Got a hot date.

127
00:09:53,889 --> 00:09:55,288
I wanna talk to you.

128
00:09:57,729 --> 00:09:59,208
Keep your mouth shut.

129
00:10:08,529 --> 00:10:11,362
- Wait. Can we talk a minute?
- No, we can't.

130
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:15,164
You said you liked scuba-diving
and raced seahorses.

131
00:10:15,369 --> 00:10:17,325
- Yes, I did.
- And you like...

132
00:10:19,689 --> 00:10:22,362
Tell me, are you involved
with anybody?

133
00:10:22,609 --> 00:10:24,088
Yes. No. Well...

134
00:10:24,329 --> 00:10:26,445
Does self-involved count?

135
00:10:28,649 --> 00:10:30,162
No phone calls.

136
00:10:30,369 --> 00:10:33,406
I left express orders
not to be disturbed.

137
00:10:33,969 --> 00:10:35,118
I'm David Basner.

138
00:10:35,329 --> 00:10:38,207
I'm looking for new
voiceover talent.

139
00:10:38,409 --> 00:10:41,082
You could be it
if I like your audition.

140
00:10:41,289 --> 00:10:43,723
Leave your name and number.
Action.

141
00:10:44,169 --> 00:10:45,648
It's Max.

142
00:10:45,849 --> 00:10:50,445
Max Basner, your father.
Maybe you heard of me.

143
00:10:50,689 --> 00:10:54,762
I thought you'd like to know
your mother left me today.

144
00:10:57,329 --> 00:10:59,843
- What?
- Oh, you're there.

145
00:11:00,049 --> 00:11:03,359
Yeah, I'm here.
What is this about Mom?

146
00:11:03,609 --> 00:11:06,407
You got a girl there?
Anybody you knew?

147
00:11:06,649 --> 00:11:08,526
Funny. What's this about Mom?

148
00:11:08,729 --> 00:11:10,287
I'm not talking English?

149
00:11:10,529 --> 00:11:13,885
Thirty-six years of marriage,
and she walks out.

150
00:11:14,089 --> 00:11:18,128
She took clothes.
She took pots, pans, the blender.

151
00:11:18,329 --> 00:11:21,048
It's 12:00 at night, and I'm alone...

152
00:11:21,249 --> 00:11:25,401
...with a meatloaf in tinfoil.
- It's a misunderstanding.

153
00:11:25,609 --> 00:11:27,679
It's not a misunderstanding.

154
00:11:27,889 --> 00:11:31,928
A misunderstanding, you take
a toothbrush, not the blender.

155
00:11:32,129 --> 00:11:34,040
Look, I'm...

156
00:11:34,249 --> 00:11:37,719
I'm in the middle of something.
Can I call you back?

157
00:11:47,449 --> 00:11:49,326
Did your mom leave your dad?

158
00:11:49,889 --> 00:11:51,527
I guess so.

159
00:11:55,369 --> 00:11:58,600
People just can't seem to
relate anymore.

160
00:12:09,689 --> 00:12:10,599
Bye-bye.

161
00:12:16,369 --> 00:12:19,361
Hello, Mrs. Packanak.
How are the birds?

162
00:12:34,009 --> 00:12:35,965
- Who is it?
- David.

163
00:12:36,169 --> 00:12:38,239
You know where the key is.

164
00:12:55,129 --> 00:12:56,528
Good morning.

165
00:13:06,249 --> 00:13:07,762
You all right?

166
00:13:08,009 --> 00:13:10,079
Never felt better.

167
00:13:14,809 --> 00:13:16,527
So, what's going on?

168
00:13:16,969 --> 00:13:21,281
I got a horse here that cannot lose.

169
00:13:22,249 --> 00:13:26,003
- Am I crazy, or is something burning?
- You're going crazy.

170
00:13:27,409 --> 00:13:30,640
You like what your mother did
with the furniture?

171
00:13:31,369 --> 00:13:33,007
Your mother's a thief.

172
00:13:33,209 --> 00:13:36,918
She took the sofa,
the easy chair, the dining table.

173
00:13:37,129 --> 00:13:39,359
I gotta eat off the card table.

174
00:13:39,569 --> 00:13:42,083
I shuffled the toast this morning.

175
00:13:43,809 --> 00:13:45,242
What is this?

176
00:13:46,769 --> 00:13:48,202
It's a steak.

177
00:13:50,809 --> 00:13:53,846
Here, I'll make another one
for myself.

178
00:13:54,049 --> 00:13:56,324
What's with you and Mom?

179
00:13:56,529 --> 00:14:01,045
I can never find the ketchup.
Where does she hide the ketchup?

180
00:14:01,929 --> 00:14:04,648
I haven't lived here in 10 years.

181
00:14:04,849 --> 00:14:08,603
She kept the peanut butter
on the top shelf. Try there.

182
00:14:09,089 --> 00:14:10,078
Here it is.

183
00:14:10,289 --> 00:14:13,645
Your mother hated me using ketchup.
She couldn't cook.

184
00:14:13,889 --> 00:14:17,768
You know, the dog didn't die.
He committed suicide.

185
00:14:18,409 --> 00:14:20,559
Now that's a piece of meat.

186
00:14:20,769 --> 00:14:22,839
Want anything for breakfast?

187
00:14:24,969 --> 00:14:26,448
So...

188
00:14:26,649 --> 00:14:28,162
...Mom left?

189
00:14:28,369 --> 00:14:30,405
Do you see anyone else here?

190
00:14:31,249 --> 00:14:34,878
Will you tell me, or are we
gonna play 20 questions?

191
00:14:35,849 --> 00:14:38,921
I told you.
She walked out, she left.

192
00:14:39,529 --> 00:14:41,281
Do you know where she is?

193
00:14:41,529 --> 00:14:43,042
Who cares?

194
00:14:44,529 --> 00:14:46,759
I'm better off without her.

195
00:14:47,849 --> 00:14:50,568
She was some bundle of fun, that one.

196
00:14:50,769 --> 00:14:53,408
My sides still hurt from laughing.

197
00:14:54,689 --> 00:14:57,920
It's not your problem.
I won't waste your time.

198
00:14:58,129 --> 00:14:59,881
Be fair.

199
00:15:00,209 --> 00:15:04,327
I hear from you three times.
For Christmas, hockey tickets...

200
00:15:04,569 --> 00:15:07,288
...and "your mother has left me."

201
00:15:07,529 --> 00:15:10,726
You wanna leave.
You been here 10 minutes already.

202
00:15:11,129 --> 00:15:13,438
Got a blond on the other pillow?

203
00:15:13,689 --> 00:15:16,965
A redhead in jeans
with the name across the ass?

204
00:15:17,289 --> 00:15:21,123
When I was a kid we didn't need
a name, just an ass.

205
00:15:23,289 --> 00:15:25,200
Go on, get out of here.

206
00:15:59,969 --> 00:16:01,607
Cut! Cut!

207
00:16:01,809 --> 00:16:03,208
What is going on here?!

208
00:16:03,569 --> 00:16:05,366
What's down here?

209
00:16:05,609 --> 00:16:08,442
- Why are my glasses on the set?
- What?

210
00:16:08,689 --> 00:16:10,884
Listen honey, it's "Jeu de paume."

211
00:16:11,089 --> 00:16:13,649
- It's not "Jeu de roller-derby."
- He moved.

212
00:16:13,849 --> 00:16:16,602
You're ripping his face off.
Take five.

213
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,083
Take a break.

214
00:16:18,289 --> 00:16:19,961
Seven minutes to lunch?

215
00:16:20,169 --> 00:16:23,320
You said yes to the Sony,
no to the drunk driving.

216
00:16:23,569 --> 00:16:25,639
- Jane wants you.
- I'll be back.

217
00:16:25,849 --> 00:16:28,647
- Talk to me.
- Lunch at Spiages.

218
00:16:28,849 --> 00:16:31,124
The no-tie meeting's at 2:30.

219
00:16:31,329 --> 00:16:33,638
- Donna call?
- I left three messages.

220
00:16:33,849 --> 00:16:36,363
Someone claiming to be your mother...

221
00:16:36,569 --> 00:16:39,686
- Wait. My mother?
- She said she was.

222
00:16:39,889 --> 00:16:42,403
I didn't know you had parents.

223
00:16:42,649 --> 00:16:45,766
- Get her on the phone.
- There's just an address.

224
00:16:45,969 --> 00:16:48,722
I've got seven layouts.

225
00:16:48,929 --> 00:16:51,204
Rog, we can't break this long.

226
00:16:51,409 --> 00:16:54,128
- Break's over.
- Thanks. Just nod at me.

227
00:16:54,329 --> 00:16:58,686
The client sees me telling you
that smoke won't cover the product.

228
00:16:58,889 --> 00:17:01,164
Find out exactly where this is.

229
00:17:16,089 --> 00:17:19,047
I rented the apartment from Lucille.

230
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:22,526
She was our cleaning lady
when you were 6.

231
00:17:22,729 --> 00:17:25,243
My mind was cluttered when I was 6.

232
00:17:26,009 --> 00:17:29,081
- Say hello to Lucille, David.
- Hello, David.

233
00:17:29,289 --> 00:17:31,325
- Good seeing you.
- You too.

234
00:17:31,569 --> 00:17:34,447
- Meet my husband, Arthur.
- How do you do?

235
00:17:35,729 --> 00:17:37,799
Oh, yeah, I remember Lucille.

236
00:17:38,009 --> 00:17:40,000
She was a little taller.

237
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:45,121
After 36 years of being married,
you pretend it didn't happen?

238
00:17:45,329 --> 00:17:46,967
Is that it, Mom?

239
00:17:52,689 --> 00:17:54,839
Is that what your father said?

240
00:17:55,049 --> 00:17:57,722
I just walked out all of a sudden?

241
00:17:58,409 --> 00:18:01,401
No, he didn't.
We just looked for ketchup.

242
00:18:01,649 --> 00:18:06,040
You don't know what it was like
since you moved away.

243
00:18:06,529 --> 00:18:08,759
There was nobody to talk to.

244
00:18:08,969 --> 00:18:12,325
He came home
and there was still nobody to talk to.

245
00:18:12,569 --> 00:18:16,847
I'd check his club chair.
That's how I knew he was home.

246
00:18:17,049 --> 00:18:22,043
I didn't leave because of the yelling.
I left because of the silence.

247
