We're excited
about the acquisition.

1219
01:29:38,409 --> 01:29:42,197
But it's a tiny part of the fleet
compared to others.

1220
01:29:42,409 --> 01:29:45,606
We showed that you have
more short flights...

1221
01:29:45,809 --> 01:29:49,119
...than any other carrier.
Next question?

1222
01:29:49,409 --> 01:29:52,799
We have a perfect safety record.
You didn't say that.

1223
01:29:53,009 --> 01:29:54,408
It could backfire.

1224
01:29:54,609 --> 01:29:58,363
People think it's luck and wonder
when it will run out.

1225
01:29:58,609 --> 01:30:02,648
We'll use it, but not in mass market.
It's too iffy.

1226
01:30:02,849 --> 01:30:04,487
Suppose we insisted.

1227
01:30:04,689 --> 01:30:06,839
- I'd say no.
- Lf you couldn't?

1228
01:30:07,049 --> 01:30:10,837
I'd walk away. It's a bad move.
I won't be responsible.

1229
01:30:11,049 --> 01:30:14,962
Good enough.
Who cares about safety records?

1230
01:30:15,209 --> 01:30:18,440
This man has a campaign to do.

1231
01:30:18,689 --> 01:30:22,125
This campaign will knock
them on their duff!

1232
01:30:22,569 --> 01:30:25,766
You've got an hour to
meet me at the airport.

1233
01:30:25,969 --> 01:30:28,437
We have the presentation in
New York.

1234
01:30:28,649 --> 01:30:31,721
Oh, yeah, that would be today.

1235
01:30:31,929 --> 01:30:35,126
I'm sorry, I can't make it.
Mustard.

1236
01:30:35,329 --> 01:30:36,808
What?

1237
01:30:37,009 --> 01:30:39,443
I'm not going. My father is ill.

1238
01:30:40,049 --> 01:30:41,960
Well, put him in a hospital.

1239
01:30:42,169 --> 01:30:46,560
I did. But he needs surgery,
and I want to be there.

1240
01:30:46,769 --> 01:30:47,804
Why?

1241
01:30:49,289 --> 01:30:50,847
Why?

1242
01:30:51,049 --> 01:30:53,085
I said we have a meeting.

1243
01:30:53,289 --> 01:30:56,645
I heard you, twice.
I told you I'm not going.

1244
01:30:56,849 --> 01:30:59,727
- Where's Charlie Gargas?
- In Los Angeles.

1245
01:31:00,609 --> 01:31:01,519
Call him.

1246
01:31:01,729 --> 01:31:03,765
- He'll be back this...
- Now!

1247
01:31:03,969 --> 01:31:07,882
Mr. Woolridge, Ted Geller can go.

1248
01:31:08,089 --> 01:31:10,603
- I hired you.
- He's familiar with it.

1249
01:31:10,809 --> 01:31:12,128
Can you talk to him?

1250
01:31:12,329 --> 01:31:16,607
Basner, you have to make the
presentation to our board.

1251
01:31:16,809 --> 01:31:19,846
You have good doctors,
you don't have to stay.

1252
01:31:20,329 --> 01:31:23,878
No, I don't, but I'm going to.

1253
01:31:24,169 --> 01:31:26,125
You're not going to New York?

1254
01:31:26,329 --> 01:31:28,081
I'm not going to New York.

1255
01:31:28,289 --> 01:31:31,201
Look, I'm serious.
I've had enough of this.

1256
01:31:31,409 --> 01:31:32,808
If you want this...

1257
01:31:33,009 --> 01:31:36,718
...you'll get up
off your ass, get packed...

1258
01:31:36,929 --> 01:31:38,328
I'm counting now.

1259
01:31:38,569 --> 01:31:39,888
One!

1260
01:31:40,409 --> 01:31:41,444
Two!

1261
01:31:41,929 --> 01:31:43,999
- Three!
- Jesus Christ!

1262
01:31:44,209 --> 01:31:45,005
Four!

1263
01:31:45,209 --> 01:31:47,848
- He really is counting.
- Five! Six!

1264
01:31:48,049 --> 01:31:51,280
This is the 20th century.
Sir, I'm not...

1265
01:31:51,529 --> 01:31:53,520
...a shit-kicker from your farm.

1266
01:31:53,729 --> 01:31:55,640
Ten!

1267
01:31:55,849 --> 01:31:57,999
Look, I'm done! Take my stuff!

1268
01:31:58,209 --> 01:31:59,961
Do what you want...

1269
01:32:00,169 --> 01:32:02,080
...but I'm not going!

1270
01:32:02,289 --> 01:32:05,725
And don't you ever
fucking touch me again!

1271
01:32:14,049 --> 01:32:15,562
Fire him.

1272
01:32:27,329 --> 01:32:28,648
Quite a show.

1273
01:32:28,849 --> 01:32:32,603
What do you do for an encore?
Burn down a building?

1274
01:32:36,969 --> 01:32:39,039
Did you just make a joke?

1275
01:32:40,009 --> 01:32:42,728
You did, didn't you?
You made a joke.

1276
01:32:42,929 --> 01:32:46,001
Not a great joke,
but you made a joke.

1277
01:32:46,209 --> 01:32:47,358
Cheryl Ann!

1278
01:32:47,609 --> 01:32:50,840
You made light of a heavy situation!
Sense of humor!

1279
01:32:51,049 --> 01:32:54,519
You do, you have one.

1280
01:32:54,729 --> 01:32:57,243
I worked damn hard on this with you.

1281
01:32:57,449 --> 01:33:00,247
I thought that
you were a professional.

1282
01:33:00,449 --> 01:33:02,167
I'm as committed as you.

1283
01:33:02,369 --> 01:33:05,679
I'm going to New York.
You're staying.

1284
01:33:05,889 --> 01:33:08,449
- We have different priorities.
- We do.

1285
01:33:08,649 --> 01:33:11,846
I'm surprised too.
I thought we were the same.

1286
01:33:12,929 --> 01:33:15,921
That's what's sad.
We were a good team.

1287
01:33:16,129 --> 01:33:19,678
I looked forward to seeing you
every morning.

1288
01:33:19,889 --> 01:33:23,438
Wondering what you'd wear,
what you'd say...

1289
01:33:23,689 --> 01:33:27,443
...and how you were gonna tease me...

1290
01:33:27,689 --> 01:33:30,567
...and when we'd
find time to make love.

1291
01:33:31,769 --> 01:33:34,886
You made all
of these exhausting hours fun.

1292
01:33:35,849 --> 01:33:38,807
That I'm gonna miss.
It's hard to find.

1293
01:33:42,929 --> 01:33:45,727
I'll miss you, David.

1294
01:33:45,929 --> 01:33:47,601
Very much.

1295
01:33:55,609 --> 01:33:57,327
You're fired.

1296
01:34:02,089 --> 01:34:05,684
You know, I liked
being with you too.

1297
01:34:05,889 --> 01:34:09,768
You're gonna make a lucky
corporation one hell of a CEO.

1298
01:34:10,129 --> 01:34:12,563
Ms. Wayne, your limo's waiting.

1299
01:34:15,089 --> 01:34:17,319
I do hope your father's okay.

1300
01:34:19,369 --> 01:34:20,688
Where are my copies?

1301
01:34:20,889 --> 01:34:22,925
On my desk, I'll meet you there.

1302
01:34:30,609 --> 01:34:33,248
Hey, will you get out?
I'm creating.

1303
01:34:33,449 --> 01:34:36,725
This is where I do my best work.
Get out!

1304
01:34:36,929 --> 01:34:38,920
Oh, it's only the boss.

1305
01:34:41,289 --> 01:34:42,517
I was sleeping.

1306
01:34:42,729 --> 01:34:45,368
I'm sorry I was gone.
I missed the fireworks.

1307
01:34:45,609 --> 01:34:48,965
You know everyone in L.A.
Has odd-colored hair?

1308
01:34:49,169 --> 01:34:51,444
I saw someone that drew it in.

1309
01:34:51,649 --> 01:34:55,085
Here I am buying hair.
I'll never understand L.A.

1310
01:34:55,289 --> 01:34:57,166
Did we lose the account?

1311
01:34:57,369 --> 01:34:59,678
No, I calmed Woolridge down.

1312
01:34:59,889 --> 01:35:03,040
I told him that I'd throw you
out of a plane...

1313
01:35:03,249 --> 01:35:05,638
...you know,
the usual punishment.

1314
01:35:05,849 --> 01:35:07,805
I'm not a partner by accident.

1315
01:35:08,009 --> 01:35:11,160
I'll apologize to you.
But not to anyone else.

1316
01:35:11,369 --> 01:35:14,247
It's been hard to
deal with all of this.

1317
01:35:16,169 --> 01:35:17,841
Join the club.

1318
01:35:22,929 --> 01:35:24,248
At the end...

1319
01:35:26,449 --> 01:35:30,567
...my dad was in a home.
It was the best in Illinois.

1320
01:35:30,769 --> 01:35:33,567
I was too busy to visit him much.

1321
01:35:33,769 --> 01:35:36,567
But I figured he was well cared-for.

1322
01:35:36,769 --> 01:35:40,284
He was a little senile.
Not much.

1323
01:35:43,409 --> 01:35:46,526
When I got around to seeing him...

1324
01:35:46,729 --> 01:35:49,527
...he didn't recognize me until he died.

1325
01:35:51,129 --> 01:35:53,689
He didn't remember who I was.

1326
01:35:56,409 --> 01:35:59,799
I thought you'd be
the perfect son, Charlie.

1327
01:36:00,729 --> 01:36:04,563
No, they tell me there
was only one of those guys.

1328
01:36:07,249 --> 01:36:09,604
You take care of what you've got...

1329
01:36:09,809 --> 01:36:11,845
...l'll take care of Woolridge.

1330
01:36:12,049 --> 01:36:13,528
Thanks.

1331
01:36:20,889 --> 01:36:23,403
I brought you some stuff from home.

1332
01:36:23,649 --> 01:36:24,968
Okay, all finished.

1333
01:36:25,449 --> 01:36:27,917
Thank you, Harvey. Wait a minute.

1334
01:36:28,129 --> 01:36:30,723
Here. Have a pen.

1335
01:36:30,929 --> 01:36:32,681
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

1336
01:36:32,889 --> 01:36:34,720
- You're welcome.
- Bye-bye.

1337
01:36:40,049 --> 01:36:41,323
You'll be fine.

1338
01:36:41,569 --> 01:36:44,447
Just as long as you aren't my doctor.

1339
01:36:44,689 --> 01:36:47,886
Come on, I could have
been a great doctor.

1340
01:36:48,089 --> 01:36:50,922
You could have been
a great anything.

1341
01:36:55,729 --> 01:36:57,367
Today was crazy at work.

1342
01:36:57,609 --> 01:36:59,804
But I'll be here.
I'm gonna go...

1343
01:37:00,009 --> 01:37:01,488
...get cleaned up...

1344
01:37:01,689 --> 01:37:06,365
...and I'll be here tomorrow.
I'll be here when you get back.

1345
01:37:06,609 --> 01:37:08,839
In other words, you'll be here.

1346
01:37:12,249 --> 01:37:15,127
Why don't you go now,
so I can sleep.

1347
01:37:15,329 --> 01:37:17,240
Or I'll be grumpy tomorrow...

1348
01:37:17,449 --> 01:37:20,088
...and I won't enjoy the operation.

1349
01:37:20,889 --> 01:37:23,039
Well, see you tomorrow.

1350
01:38:13,969 --> 01:38:18,121
I don't have any blood left,
so you can get out.

1351
01:38:37,089 --> 01:38:39,284
I was in the neighborhood.

1352
01:38:43,009 --> 01:38:45,443
What's new?
How are you doing?

1353
01:38:46,369 --> 01:38:49,042
Fine. I'm doing fine.

1354
01:38:50,089 --> 01:38:52,523
I take your word for it.

1355
01:38:53,929 --> 01:38:55,681
Can I offer you something?

1356
01:38:55,889 --> 01:38:59,768
Cookie? Glass of water?
Some morphine?

1357
01:39:00,649 --> 01:39:03,038
Thank you. I'll take a cookie.

1358
01:39:03,249 --> 01:39:04,728
David brought them.

1359
01:39:04,969 --> 01:39:08,405
They're that delicious diabetic kind.

1360
01:39:08,849 --> 01:39:11,568
It's all they'll
let me eat around here.

1361
01:39:12,249 --> 01:39:15,924
I could be dead tomorrow.
They're putting me on a diet.

1362
01:39:17,249 --> 01:39:20,002
I can still make you laugh, can't I?

1363
01:39:20,609 --> 01:39:25,160
When you wanted to, you could make me
laugh. Right from the beginning.

1364
01:39:25,649 --> 01:39:27,879
I was one charming guy, wasn't I?

1365
01:39:28,089 --> 01:39:31,001
- To everybody except my mother.
- Shit.

1366
01:39:33,569 --> 01:39:35,161
What were we, Max?

1367
01:39:35,369 --> 01:39:40,079
Two kids who thought if you went
on a couple of dates, you got married.

1368
01:39:40,289 --> 01:39:44,521
What couple of dates?
We went out eight or nine times!

1369
01:39:44,729 --> 01:39:46,685
We had plenty of laughs.

1370
01:39:46,889 --> 01:39:50,325
I tried to teach you how
to drive that old Hudson.

1371
01:39:57,409 --> 01:40:01,846
I wish there were more
things like that.

1372
01:40:02,209 --> 01:40:04,279
More moments.

1373
01:40:05,889 --> 01:40:10,201
We lived together a long time, Max,
but we were never friends.

1374
01:40:11,409 --> 01:40:14,799
Lorraine, you didn't know
how to have fun.

1375
01:40:15,009 --> 01:40:17,159
- Why didn't you teach me?
- I tried.

1376
01:40:17,369 --> 01:40:21,840
- I tried a million goddamn times!
- No, just a few times!

1377
01:40:22,049 --> 01:40:25,564
- Then you just gave up on me.
- You did the same thing!

1378
01:40:32,809 --> 01:40:35,277
Why didn't we talk, Max?

1379
01:40:35,529 --> 01:40:38,680
Why didn't we tell each other
how we felt?

1380
01:40:41,409 --> 01:40:44,003
Do you know what we were, Max?

1381
01:40:44,929 --> 01:40:47,523
We were roommates.

1382
01:40:49,369 --> 01:40:53,362
Goddamn you for doing what
you did to yourself!

1383
01:40:53,849 --> 01:40:56,124
What you did to us.

1384
01:40:57,049 --> 01:41:00,598
Oh, God, what happened to us, Max?

1385
01:41:01,649 --> 01:41:03,719
I cared.

1386
01:41:04,729 --> 01:41:06,367
I know I cared.

1387
01:41:10,049 --> 01:41:11,687
Bullshit.

1388
01:42:09,569 --> 01:42:11,048
I'm here, Dad.

1389
01:42:11,249 --> 01:42:12,967
You're here.

1390
01:42:22,649 --> 01:42:24,879
It's a Honduran, Dad.

1391
01:42:25,929 --> 01:42:29,888
In case they give you
time for a smoke break.

1392
01:42:37,529 --> 01:42:40,760
Excuse me.
We have to take him to surgery now.

1393
01:43:42,809 --> 01:43:46,882
You look so distinguished, Charlie.
It's coming along great.

1394
01:43:47,329 --> 01:43:50,765
Could we have some makeup?
We have a bit of a shine.

1395
01:43:51,129 --> 01:43:52,039
Thanks.

1396
01:43:52,409 --> 01:43:55,640
- Everyone must leave. He has a call.
- I'll be back.

1397
01:43:55,849 --> 01:43:58,886
- Everybody, let's take five minutes.
- Thank you.

1398
01:44:04,649 --> 01:44:07,117
David, how is he?

1399
01:44:07,409 --> 01:44:10,003
He lost his toes
and part of one foot...

1400
01:44:10,209 --> 01:44:12,848
...but he can walk again
with a cane.

1401
01:44:14,769 --> 01:44:18,887
Thank God it wasn't worse.
When are you coming back to work?

1402
01:44:19,089 --> 01:44:21,762
You're missing my photos
with a naked head.

1403
01:44:23,769 --> 01:44:25,760
I don't know.

1404
01:44:25,969 --> 01:44:28,244
I don't know, Charlie.

1405
01:44:28,849 --> 01:44:32,967
Why don't you give my accounts
to Ted Geller till I come back.

1406
01:44:33,449 --> 01:44:36,168
Babysitting him will drive you crazy.

1407
01:44:38,129 --> 01:44:39,528
Well, maybe.

1408
01:44:39,729 --> 01:44:41,799
But I want to get to know him.

1409
01:44:42,009 --> 01:44:45,319
You never know, he may get
to know me a little too.

1410
01:44:47,729 --> 01:44:48,718
Good luck.

1411
01:44:50,129 --> 01:44:52,040
Thanks, Charlie.

1412
01:44:52,809 --> 01:44:56,040
Don't give up my window.

1413
01:44:56,649 --> 01:44:58,048
Bye-bye.

1414
01:45:08,329 --> 01:45:12,038
- They'll put him to bed soon, sir.
- Thank you.

1415
01:45:58,889 --> 01:46:03,280
I filled the refrigerator, so there
will be food when he comes home.

1416
01:46:03,529 --> 01:46:06,202
And I have some keys for you.

1417
01:46:06,409 --> 01:46:09,207
You'll be needing a second set.

1418
01:46:09,409 --> 01:46:11,365
I won't be coming back.

1419
01:46:14,729 --> 01:46:17,926
Your father might not
get any better, David.

1420
01:46:18,609 --> 01:46:21,760
He's going to need a lot of care.

1421
01:46:23,969 --> 01:46:26,324
I can't...

1422
01:46:26,929 --> 01:46:30,080
I mean, he and I, it's just...

1423
01:46:30,609 --> 01:46:33,077
...impossible.

1424
01:46:33,289 --> 01:46:35,120
It just doesn't work.

1425
01:46:35,889 --> 01:46:37,766
I know, Mom.

1426
01:46:40,809 --> 01:46:43,039
Do you hate me for that?

1427
01:46:44,569 --> 01:46:46,002
No.

1428
01:46:46,609 --> 01:46:49,169
I do not hate you.
You're my mom.

1429
01:46:52,689 --> 01:46:54,327
Call me.

1430
01:47:15,969 --> 01:47:17,561
- Go get the car.
- Yeah.

1431
01:47:17,769 --> 01:47:20,920
- The blue station wagon, right?
- Thanks.

1432
01:47:23,529 --> 01:47:25,087
I found you.

1433
01:47:25,769 --> 01:47:30,206
- I'm taking Max home today.
- Your mother told me.

1434
01:47:30,729 --> 01:47:34,324
- Thank you for coming around so much.
- That's okay.

1435
01:47:34,569 --> 01:47:35,922
You're welcome.

1436
01:47:36,329 --> 01:47:37,762
For your theater?

1437
01:47:37,969 --> 01:47:40,437
- The school donated them.
- All three?

1438
01:47:40,689 --> 01:47:42,839
Well, it's a start.

1439
01:47:43,049 --> 01:47:46,883
The kids went to get my car.
I parked in Detroit.

1440
01:47:49,689 --> 01:47:53,045
You're the only girl I dated
that my parents liked.

1441
01:47:53,969 --> 01:47:58,167
I'm the only girl you dated
that your parents ever met.

1442
01:48:09,529 --> 01:48:11,599
This is comfortable.

1443
01:48:22,289 --> 01:48:24,723
This is very comfortable.

1444
01:48:31,449 --> 01:48:33,758
I think so too.

1445
01:48:51,409 --> 01:48:56,358
- Your son bought you a nice outfit.
- He's always buying me something.

1446
01:48:56,609 --> 01:49:00,124
- Good luck. Thanks for the pen.
- You're welcome, Gina.

1447
01:49:00,329 --> 01:49:04,845
We're signed out. Paid the bill.
Do you people work on commission?

1448
01:49:05,049 --> 01:49:08,564
- The orderly will be at the elevator.
- Thank you.

1449
01:49:17,009 --> 01:49:17,964
You all right?

1450
01:49:20,089 --> 01:49:22,205
That Gina gives a good sponge.

1451
01:49:23,249 --> 01:49:25,126
Let's get out of here.

1452
01:49:37,449 --> 01:49:42,000
You're the last person I thought
would ever come through for me.

1453
01:54:01,729 --> 01:54:02,718
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group

